cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a novel architecture of multi-scale fully convolutional neural networks for fast PET image reconstruction, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the proposed model with simulated data and applying it to clinical PET data, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of residual connections and dilated convolutions in the proposed model also suggests that it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of molecular imaging in interventional/surgical procedures, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
